i see fangame awards from a showmanship perspective, the coolest result is what needs to happen, which is still subjective, but im not going for my opinions, because my opinions are not the coolest result
it also needs to be something others agree
my showmanship angle would be that i decide, but for each game, i interview their greatest defenders
its basically what happens at the end of iron chef
gordon ramsey always has it hard at the final decision, so he has extra voices that tell him a bunch of stuff, and he can see the biases in them, but he has to filter them
funnily enough if it was up to me, the previous awards there was an L needle game that should have won an award
but because nobody voted for it it doesnt get anything
yet cm_stone, on a community awards, wrote something better than any of the judges combined in the discord channels
its called Less is More, it did something
very interesting
its basically a puzzle game, you have all the tech from fangames, but you have the extra added that you can change your jump heights at any time
including negative heights i think
a whole needle server dedicated to solving this btw
i particularly dont care about what is supposed to be famous or not, i care about celebrating things and giving them the spotlight, and for the community awards i asked cm_stone about his experience
